The Serializable interface in Java is a marker interface that allows an object to be converted into a byte stream 
for storage, transmission, or caching, ensuring that only explicitly permitted classes can be serialized.

REST APIs use HTTP, and HTTP usually uses TCP.

Serialization options for diffferent technologies.

JMS	-> Optional (ObjectMessage = Java serialization, TextMessage = JSON)
Kafka ->	Always serialized (Avro / JSON / Protobuf / String / bytes)
gRPC-> Always serialized using Protocol Buffers

